com.att.android.arodatacollector.main
Class ARODataCollector

java.lang.Object
  android.content.Context

          android.app.Application
              com.att.android.arodatacollector.main.ARODataCollector
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.content.ComponentCallbacks
public class ARODataCollector
extends android.app.Application

Represents the ARO Data Collector application. The ARO Data Collector class provides methods for storing, getting, and setting data that is used during the life cycle of the application.

app_flurry_api_key

public java.lang.String app_flurry_api_key
Flurry Analytics API Key. This is associated to the Application specified at https://dev.flurry.com under a specified login and Company AT&T. This is the default value meant for ATT Developers. Internal ATT users will override this value via a file input.

Returns a value that indicates whether or not the video.mp4 file is created in the current trace folder.

Returns:
A boolean value that is true if the video.mp4 file exists in the current trace folder and is larger than 0 bytes. Otherwise, the value is false.

writeToFlurry

public void writeToFlurry(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> hashMapToWriteTo,

                          java.lang.String comment,
                          java.lang.String existingState,
                          java.lang.String currentState)
Writing to a Flurry hashmap if state changes but not log the event. The event should be logged at a later time.

Parameters:
hashMapToWriteTo - Hashmap to write event data to.

existingState - used to compare states, if it is the same as last state, hashmap is not updated. Displayed for logging.
currentState - Current state of Event. Displayed for logging in this method.
